 silence of having given too much for too long."}]]}]]}]]}],["$","main",null,{"className":"max-w-[1440px] mx-auto px-5 md:px-12 relative z-[1]","children":[["$","section",null,{"className":"border-b border-line","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"flex items-center gap-3 text-[11px] tracking-[0.32em] uppercase text-ink-muted font-semibold pt-10 pb-4","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"inline-block w-5 h-px bg-ink-faint"}],"Choose an emotion"]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"flex flex-wrap gap-2 md:gap-3 pb-8","children":[["$","$L4","empty-achievement",{"href":"/burnout/empty-achievement","className":"text-[14px] md:text-[15px] font-semibold tracking-[-0.005em] px-5 py-2.5 rounded-full transition-all duration-300 no-underline bg-accent text-bg shadow-[0_0_24px_rgba(19,237,255,0.35)]","children":"Empty Achievement"}],["$","$L4","compassion-fatigue",{"href":"/burnout/compassion-fatigue","className":"text-[14px] md:text-[15px] font-semibold tracking-[-0.005em] px-5 py-2.5 rounded-full transition-all duration-300 no-underline bg-white/[0.06] text-ink-soft hover:text-ink hover:bg-white/[0.10] border border-white/[0.08]","children":"Compassion Fatigue"}]]}]]}],["$","section",null,{"className":"border-b border-white/8 py-12 md:py-16","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"max-w-[720px]","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"mb-5 flex items-center gap-3","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"h-px w-6 bg-accent/60"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"text-[10px] font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.3em] text-accent/70","children":["On ","Empty Achievement"]}]]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-[16px] font-normal leading-[1.8] text-ink-soft md:text-[18px]","children":"You reached it. The thing you told yourself would make everything make sense. You stood there and waited for the feeling and the feeling did not come. This is the particular cruelty of high-achieving emptiness — it has no obvious cause, no legible reason, no one to blame. You did everything right. You built the life. And you are standing in it wondering what went wrong. These films take that experience seriously. They do not offer solutions. They offer recognition, which is the rarer and more useful gift."}]]}]}],["$","section",null,{"className":"py-16 md:py-20","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"flex flex-col md:flex-row md:items-end md:justify-between gap-6 mb-10 md:mb-14","children":[["$","div",null,{"children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"flex items-center gap-3 mb-4 text-[11px] tracking-[0.32em] uppercase text-ink-muted font-semibold","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"inline-block w-5 h-px bg-ink-faint"}],"Empty Achievement"]}],["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-[32px] md:text-[44px] lg:text-[56px] font-bold leading-[1.05] tracking-[-0.025em] text-ink max-w-[820px]","children":"Films for the summit that felt like nothing."}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"text-[12px] tracking-[0.18em] uppercase text-ink-muted font-semibold md:text-right shrink-0","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"block text-[44px] md:text-[56px] text-ink font-bold tracking-[-0.03em] normal-case leading-none","children":"10"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"mt-2 block","children":"Curated films"}]]}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"py-10 border-b border-white/6 mb-10","children":["$","$L5",null,{"films":[{"title":"Fight Club","director":"David Fincher","year":1999,"rating":9.1,"mood":"ash","story":"An insomniac office worker and a charismatic soap salesman form an underground fight club that evolves into something far darker — a film about the violence that follows emptiness.","why":"The alienation of achieving the prescribed life and finding it hollow — and what happens when someone breaks. Still the most accurate portrait of masculine emptiness at scale.","after":"You'll question every structure you've accepted without interrogating.","direction":"Fincher's kinetic, suffocating style mirrors the protagonist's mental state perfectly.","cinematography":