s perfectly calibrated contrast.","musicSound":"Mowg's score is angular, contemporary, slightly wrong. Exactly as intended.","impact":"One of the most formally precise films of its decade. Every frame means something.","overall":"A modern masterpiece from one of cinema's most underrated directors."},{"title":"The Social Network","director":"David Fincher","year":2010,"rating":9,"mood":"night","story":"The founding of Facebook, told as a legal deposition — a film about a boy who wanted to belong so badly he built the world's largest social network and still ended up alone.","why":"Achievement as displacement — building an empire out of the wound of not being wanted. Billion-dollar success that solves nothing.","after":"You'll understand that what you're building might not be what you're actually trying to build.","direction":"Fincher's signature precision — every cut, every camera move deliberate and exact.","cinematography":"Jeff Cronenweth's blue-grey Harvard winter is the loneliest campus ever filmed.","musicSound":"Trent Reznor and Atticus Ross create a score that sounds like electronic alienation.","impact":"Jesse Eisenberg's Zuckerberg is the decade's defining character — brilliant and completely alone.","overall":"Probably the definitive film about Silicon Valley ambition and the emotional vacuum beneath."},{"title":"Magnolia","director":"Paul Thomas Anderson","year":1999,"rating":9.4,"mood":"violet","story":"Nine interconnected lives in San Fernando Valley converge over one day and night — fathers and sons, ambition and regret, coincidence and consequence.","why":"The film about the price of achievement and the failure of performance — fathers who won and still lost everything that mattered.","after":"You'll forgive someone. Probably yourself.","direction":"Anderson at his most operatic — the camera as bold as a confession.","cinematography":"Robert Elswit photographs the Valley as a world of impossible distances between people.","musicSound":"Aimee Mann's songs are the emotional engine — this is a musical that doesn't know it is one.","impact":"The frogs. The \"Wise Up\" sequence. Moments that don't work on paper and devastate in practice.","overall":"Three hours of emotional truth. One of the great American films."},{"title":"Lost in America","director":"Albert Brooks","year":1985,"rating":8.4,"mood":"gold","story":"A successful advertising executive quits his job, convinces his wife to drop out of society, and discovers that dropping out is not as easy as dropping in.","why":"The fantasy of freedom that reveals itself as terror the moment it becomes available. Achievement abandoned and the vacuum that follows.","after":"You'll be relieved you didn't do what you were planning to do.","direction":"Brooks is the most precise comic filmmaker America produced in the 1980s. Not a wasted frame.","cinematography":"Eric Saarinen photographs the American road with equal amounts of love and dread.","musicSound":"Arthur B. Rubinstein's score is cheerful in a way that makes the anxiety worse.","impact":"Comedy that tells the truth about the American Dream with the precision of a scalpel.","overall":"Underrated, essential, and funnier than it has any right to be about something so sad."}],"label":"10 films — quick browse"}]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"grid grid-cols-2 gap-x-3 gap-y-5 sm:grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-3 lg:grid-cols-4 xl:grid-cols-4 sm:gap-x-5 sm:gap-y-7","children":[["$","$L6","Fight Club-1999",{"film":"$7"}],["$","$L6","American Beauty-1999",{"film":"$8"}],["$","$L6","Up in the Air-2009",{"film":"$9"}],["$","$L6","Downsizing-2017",{"film":"$a"}],["$","$L6","Paterson-2016",{"film":"$b"}],["$","$L6","About Schmidt-2002",{"film":"$c"}],["$","$L6","Burning-2018",{"film":"$d"}],["$","$L6","The Social Network-2010",{"film":"$e"}],["$","$L6","Magnolia-1999",{"film":"$f"}],["$","$L6","Lost in America-1985",{"film":"$10"}]]}]]}],["$","section",null,{"className":"py-14 md:py-16 border-t border-line","children":[["$","div",nu